Project Admin (Talent Pool)

   26 Sep 2013 03:09 PM - Saudi Arabia

   . Project Admin (Talent Pool)-T-SYS-PA-SA-980
   Description
   Bombardier Transportation is the number one provider of rail solutions
   in the world. Our business holds the number one global market position
   in eight of the ten markets we service. Our product portfolio includes
   a full range of passenger rail vehicles and we manufacture locomotives,
   bogies, propulsion and rail control solutions.
   At Bombardier, 70,000 employees in 60 countries work together to evolve
   mobility worldwide - one good idea at a time. If you have a good idea,
   we'll provide the environment where it will thrive and grow into a
   great product or customer experience. Your ideas are our fuel.
   We are talent pooling for Project Administrator(s) in Saudi Arabia.
   Your role
   To provide Project Management support to the project team particularly
   with respect to monitoring & reporting; ROP, CAPD, PPRS reporting and
   document control.
   Your Key Accountabilities
   - Monitoring & Controlling - Manage the day to day PMO co-ordination &
   reporting activities for example Communications; meeting calendar,
   meeting minutes, etc, chairing meetings to track progress of Risk,
   Margin Enhancement, Change. Setting-up and updating Bombardier bespoke
   PM tools; ROP, CAPD and co-ordinating PPRS inputs from functions.
   - Document Control - provide document control co-ordination role
   managing all project documentation including correspondence & technical
   documentation from internal; KSA, Pittsburgh, & external stakeholders.
   - Provide PM Administrative support to all PM site meetings: clients
   and technical advisors, Saudi Approval bodies and BT suppliers. Minute
   those meetings & formally issue and track action closure.
   - Schedule Monitoring & Progress - Co-ordinate downloading & uploading
   of revised schedule data from Pittsburgh ensuring revision status
   tracked & correct. Record changes instructed by client & after approval
   of PM to communicate to Pittsburgh.
   Qualifications
   - At least 5 years experience as document controller on major project
   within Middle East.
   - Experience of Information Systems, Excel 2007, Word 2007 and
   Microsoft Planner or Primavera essential.
   - Experience of PM process; time, scope, change and risk management
   essential.
   - Knowledge of Bombardier Project Management process/procedures
   desirable.
   - Candidates must be fluent in English and additional knowledge of
   Arabic will be an advantage.
   We thank all applicants for their interest; however, only those under
   consideration will be contacted.
   We are looking for great professionals to join us. For more information
   about our projects, products or if you want to 'meet' with our core
   project teams, please join our group on LinkedIn - Bombardier
   Transportation - The Gulf Network
